  "title": "What to say when you fear you may afflict something with the evil eye",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 244",
  "arabic": "إِذَا رَأَى أَحَدُكُم مِنْ أَخِيهِ أَوْ مِنْ نَفْسِهِ أَوْ مِنْ مَالِهِ مَا يُعْجِبُهُ فَلْيَدْعُ لَهُ بِالْبَرَكَةِ فَإِنَّ الْعَيْنَ حَقٌّ",
  "meaning": "If you see anything of your brother that pleases you, or of his person or of his property [then ask Allah to bless him in it] for the envious eye is real.",
